# Environment Configuration Guide

## Local Development (XAMPP)
No additional configuration needed. The app automatically detects localhost and uses local settings.

## Azure Cloud Deployment

Set the following environment variables in Azure App Service Configuration:

### Database Variables
- `DB_HOST`: Your database server host (e.g., `your-server.postgres.database.azure.com`)
- `DB_USER`: Database username
- `DB_PASS`: Database password
- `DB_NAME`: Database name (e.g., `evinty_ecommerce`)

### Site Variables
- `SITE_EMAIL`: Contact email for the site
- `SITE_URL`: (Optional) Will be auto-detected from the domain

### Example Azure CLI command to set variables:
```bash
az webapp config appsettings set \
  --resource-group <resource-group> \
  --name <app-name> \
  --settings \
    DB_HOST="your-db-host.postgres.database.azure.com" \
    DB_USER="dbuser@server" \
    DB_PASS="your-password" \
    DB_NAME="evinty_ecommerce" \
    SITE_EMAIL="admin@again-co.com"
```

### Setup Instructions:
1. The `web.config` file handles URL rewriting for IIS/Azure App Service
2. The `.htaccess` file provides Apache compatibility for testing
3. Configuration is environment-aware and uses PHP getenv() for Azure variables
4. Error logs in production mode are stored in `/logs/error.log`
